The paper deals with image manipulation and forgery detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of deep learning models and unsupervised domain adaptation networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses the challenges involved in detecting copy-move forgery, which is a type of image tampering, indicating that it may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper proposes the creation of a synthetic dataset, which involves image processing techniques, suggesting that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
